%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFor%20decades%2C%20California%20has%20struggled%20with%20a%20persistent%20affordable%20housing%20shortage.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20WSJ%20report%20detailed%20how%20one%20LA%20housing%20project%20was%20unable%20to%20get%20off%20the%20ground%20for%20over%2015%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELos%20Angeles%20Mayor%20Karen%20Bass%20has%20made%20it%20a%20priority%20to%20obtain%20project%20approvals%20in%20a%20timely%20manner.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELos%20Angeles%20has%20long%20attracted%20new%20residents%20with%20its%20warm%20weather%2C%20abundant%20outdoor%20amenities%2C%20and%20the%20lure%20of%20opportunities%20in%20the%20media%20and%20entertainment%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20state%20of%20California%20has%20also%20become%20widely%20known%20for%20its%20severe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-population-growth-central-valley-bay-area-housing-affordability-exodus-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehousing%20crunch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20affordability%20being%20the%20leading%20issue%20that%20has%20driven%20many%20natives%20and%20longtime%20residents%20to%20inland%20communities%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaving-california-moving-to-las-vegas-living-in-seattle-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elower-cost%20states%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Freal-estate%2Fhousing-affordable-building-real-estate-db1d696e%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20California's%20complex%20regulations%20have%20played%20a%20major%20role%20in%20delaying%20the%20construction%20of%20a%2049-unit%20apartment%20complex%20known%20as%20Lorena%20Plaza%20in%20the%20Boyle%20Heights%20neighborhood%20east%20of%20downtown%20Los%20Angeles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202007%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20Community%20of%20Friends%2C%20a%20local%20nonprofit%20organization%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewas%20given%20land%20to%20build%20a%20small%20affordable%20housing%20development%2C%20but%20construction%20on%20the%20project%20only%20began%20roughly%20a%20year%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20project%20was%20slowed%20down%20by%20the%20need%20for%20various%20approvals%20from%20politicians%20and%20commissions%20and%20higher%20construction%20costs%20caused%20by%20multiple%20delays%2C%20the%20Journal%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city%20wants%20to%20build%20450%2C000%20new%20units%20of%20housing%20by%202029%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fopinion%2Fstory%2F2022-02-20%2Feditorial-los-angeles-new-mayor-homelessness%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Los%20Angeles%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20absence%20of%20housing%20remains%20a%20significant%20obstacle%20for%20many%20Angelenos%20right%20now.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lahsa.org%2Fnews%3Farticle%3D927-lahsa-releases-results-of-2023-greater-los-angeles-homeless-count%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELos%20Angeles%20Homeless%20Services%20Authority%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20their%202023%20report%2C%20estimated%20that%20roughly%2046%2C000%20people%20in%20the%20city%20are%20experiencing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lahsa.org%2Fnews%3Farticle%3D927-lahsa-releases-results-of-2023-greater-los-angeles-homeless-count%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomelessness%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20any%20given%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELos%20Angeles%20Mayor%20Karen%20Bass%2C%20a%20former%20congresswoman%20who%20this%20month%20completed%20her%20first%20year%20in%20City%20Hall%2C%20said%20last%20December%20that%20the%20glacial%20pace%20of%20progress%20regarding%20Lorena%20Plaza%20was%20emblematic%20of%20policies%20she%20sought%20to%20reshape%20as%20mayor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20on%20earth%20could%20we%20expect%20to%20house%2040%2C000%20%5Bhomeless%5D%20people%20if%20we%20con