Nambiew-1700660339-150x100.jpeg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FNambiew-1700660339-272x182.jpeg%20272w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-334692%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ENambie%20rose%20above%20hate%20to%20popularise%20Northeastern%20cuisine.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKappa%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F302187%2Fchennai-startup-electric-vehicle-two-wheelers-in-africa-electric-autos-and-e-mobility%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecooking%20technique%3C%2Fa%3E%20used%20by%20the%20Garo%20tribe%2C%20to%20which%20Nambie%20belongs%2C%20in%20which%20meat%20and%20vegetables%20are%20cooked%20using%20liquid%20alkali%20(called%20%3Cem%3Ekalchi%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20Garo).%20She%20calls%20%3Cem%3EKappa%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9Csynonymous%20with%20Northeastern%20cuisine%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20households%20in%20the%20West%20Khasi%20Hills%2C%20food%20is%20really%20simple%20and%20made%20using%20locally%20sourced%20ingredients%2C%20usually%20from%20their%20farms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20rice%20eaters%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20eat%20breakfast.%20Our%20mornings%20begin%20with%20some%20red%20or%20black%20tea.%20We%20eat%20lunch%20by%2010%20am%2C%20which%20gives%20the%20residents%2C%20mostly%20farmers%2C%20energy%20to%20work%20throughout%20the%20day.%20We%20have%20dinner%20by%205%20pm%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20eat%20a%20lot%20of%20meat%20as%20it%20gets%20very%20cold%20during%20winter.%20We%20save%20our%20meat%20and%20fish%20by%20smoking%20them.%20A%20typical%20meal%20includes%20rice%2C%20%3Cem%3Edal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20meat%20or%20dried%20fish%2C%20and%20lots%20of%20vegetables%20available%20in%20our%20backyard%20(root%2C%20wild%2C%20leafy%20vegetables)%20with%20a%20side%20of%20%3Cem%3Echutney%3C%2Fem%3E.%20We%20also%20dry%20vegetables%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20dishes%2C%20Nambie%20heroes%20ingredients%20grown%20in%20Meghalaya%20%E2%80%94%20like%20fiddlehead%20ferns%2C%20elephant%20apple%2C%20elephant%20foot%20yams%2C%20purple%20yams%2C%20Indian%20sorrel%2C%20fish%20mint%20leaves%2C%20%3Cem%3Esohiong%3C%2Fem%3E%20(blackberry)%2C%20%3Cem%3Esohplhang%20(%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20root%20vegetable)%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20makes%20%3Cem%3Echutneys%3C%2Fem%3E%20using%20ingredients%20like%20brinjal%20and%20dry%20fish%2C%20fermented%20fish%20%3Cem%3Echutney%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20dried%20roselle%20with%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Epura%20%3C%2Fem%3E(rice%20flour)%2C%20%3Cem%3Ejadoh%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20%3Cem%3EKhasi%3C%2Fem%3E%20rice%20recipe)%2C%20beef%20trotter%20soup%2C%20muskmelon%20and%20pork%20gravy%20dish%2C%20and%20much%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20she%20was%20appreciated%20by%20many%2C%20she%20also%20faced%20vicious%20trolling%20and%20hate.%20Trolls%20ridiculed%20her%20for%20cooking%20outdoors%2C%20the%20food%20she%20cooked%2C%20and%20even%20the%20fact%20that%20she%20wore%20slippers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20were%20some%20really%20harsh%20comments.%20People%20said%20things%20like%20%E2%80%9CYour%20food%20looks%20like%20dog%20food%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20are%20you%20wearing%20those%20slippers%3F%E2%80%9D.%20I%20cook%20outside%20as%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20electricity%20most%20of%20the%20time%20at%20home%2C%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20show%20our%20surroundings%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trolling%20reached%20a%20point%20where%20she%20considered%20quitting%20social%20media%20due%20to%20the%20excessive%20negativity.%20All%20she%20was%20trying%20to%20do%20was%20showcase%20her%20home%2C%20surroundings%20and%20food.%20Realising%20that%20she%20would%20let%20the%20naysayers%20win%20if%20she%20gave%20up%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20overcome%20the%20hate%20by%20growing%20a%20thick%20skin.%20She%20focused%20on%20the%20positive%20comments%2C%20which%20were%20also%20many%20in%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20decided%20to%20accept%20that%20there%20will%20be%20negativity%20and%20people%20trying%20to%20pull%20you%20down.%20What%20matters%20is%20that%20you%20should%20believe%20in%20what%20you%20do.%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20let%20the%20haters%20win.%20What%20I%E2%80%99m%20doing%20is%20trying%20to%20showcase%20my%20cuisine%20and%20break%20the%20stereotypes%20associated%20with%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20overcame%20the%20xenophobia%20and%20became%20a%20harbinger%20for%20many%20more%20YouTubers%20from%20the%20Northeast%2C%20which%20led%20to%20her%20cementing%20a%20position%20in%20MasterChef%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EProviding%20a%20new%20lease%20of%20life%20to%20children%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FCgJotPrDIeJ%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FCgJotPrDIeJ%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FCgJotPrDIeJ%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20Nambie%20Jessica%20Marak%20(%40eatyourkappa)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20her%20YouTube%20channel%20was%20flourishing%2C%20she%20had%20to%20move%20back%20home%20as%20her%20mother%20was%20ill.%20In%202019%2C%20she%20packed%20her%20bags%20and%20moved%20to%20Upper%20Rangsa%20with%20her%20infant%20daughter.%20A%20few%20months%20later%2C%20her%20husband%2C%20also%20a%20teacher%2C%20packed%20his%20bags%2C%20quit%20his%20job%20and%20followed%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeing%20the%20two%20most%20educated%20people%20in%20the%20entire%20village%20of%20150%20people%2C%20they%20were%20soon%20presented%20with%20an%20opportunity%20to%20create%20change%2C%20when%20a%20private%20school%20in%20the%20neighbouring%20village%20was%20about%20to%20shut%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLast%20year%2C%20the%20person%20running%20the%20school%20found%20it%20difficult%20to%20manage%20the%20school.%20He%20abandoned%20the%20school%20and%20the%20children%20and%20left.%20The%20village%20head%20came%20to%20us%20and%20asked%20us%20to%20help%20as%20it%20is%20the%20only%20school%20for%20the%20children%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Nambie.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOffered%20a%20school%20on%20a%20plate%20and%20a%20chance%20to%20help%20villagers%2C%20the%20couple%20took%20up%20the%20challenge.%20They%20adopted%20the%20school%20and%20the%2019%20students%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20village%20sits%20near%20the%20border%2C%20and%20with%20poor%20roads%2C%20commuting%20to%20schools%20outside%20daily%20isn%E2%80%99t%20feasible.%20If%20this%20school%20closes%2C%20it%E2%80%99ll%20disrupt%20many%20farmers%E2%80%99%20lives.%20They%20might%20need%20to%20move%20to%20Assam%2C%20straining%20resources%20and%20losing%20their%20income.%20We%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20them%20to%20worry%20about%20where%20their%20kids%20go%20to%20school.%20We%20only%20want%20them%20to%20focus%20on%20their%20farms%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Nambie.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20year%2C%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20school%20has%20increased%20from%2019%20to%2085.%20They%20do%20this%20for%20free%2C%20only%20charging%20a%20nominal%20fee%20to%20pay%20the%20other%20teachers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20spare%20time%2C%20the%20couple%20tends%20to%20a%20farm%2C%20cultivating%20lemongrass.%20They%20sell%20lemongrass%20oil%2C%20while%20Nambie%20pursues%20her%20passion%20for%20pickling%20by%20starting%20a%20pickle%20business.%20She%20also%20dreams%20of%20opening%20a%20restaurant%20someday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20more%20important%20to%20Nambie%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F332322%2Fabha-singhaal-khichdi-express-model-cloud-kitchen-entreprenuer-business-crores%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eteaching%20or%20cooking%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20always%20been%20connected%20to%20food%20and%20I%20really%20enjoy%20being%20around%20children.%20You%20learn%20something%20new%20in%20both%20teaching%20and%20cooking.%20Every%20day%20is%20a%20new%20day%20in%20the%20kitchen%20as%20well%20as%20the%20classroom.%20I%20love%20it.%20Why%20would%20I%20choose%20between%20the%20two%3F%E2%80%9D%20laughs%20Nambie.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700662812000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FNambi2-1700662473.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D334658%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nambie%20Jessica%20Marak%20from%20Meghalaya%20created%20'Eat%20Your%20Kappa'%20on%20YouTube%20to%20showcase%20Northeastern%20culture%20and%20change%20how%20people%20view%20local%20food.%20She's%20also%20one%20of%20the%20top-eight%20final